    "long_instructions": "## AI as Creator. You as Collaborator.\r\n\r\nSwitch roles by prompting AI to make the same type of creative content that you did. Offer the AI a critique for it to revise its output. \r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Tell AI to complete the same **creative task** you did earlier\r\n   - For example, if you wrote a futuristic advertisement for a self-driving bicycle, tell the AI to ***write a futuristic advertisement for a self-driving bicycle.***\r\n2. **Record AI’s initial response** in your Activity Guide.\r\n3. **Evaluate AI’s content** based on your opinion:\r\n    - **Clarity:** Does it make sense?\r\n    - **Engagement:** Is it interesting?\r\n    - **Originality:** Does it feel creative?\r\n4. Tell AI what is **missing or weak** in the response and **prompt AI to refine** the output.\r\n    - For example, _“This doesn’t make sense. Revise it so that it does.” or “This isn’t very creative. Revise it to be more creative.”_\r\n5. **Refine AI’s output** one more time by telling the AI to adjust at least one of the following:\r\n    - **Style** (e.g., make it more persuasive, humorous, dramatic).\r\n    - **Format** (e.g., turn it into a dialogue, an infographic description).\r\n    - **Context** (e.g., add specific facts to make it more original).\r\n6. Record AI’s final **refined output** in your Activity Guide.\r\n\r\n**Try it out!**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure what format to tell the AI to refine?**]\r\nGo back to Lesson 8: Debugging and Refining Outputs in your Unit Guide to review the information on the **Five Key Elements of a Prompt:**\r\n- **Task** - Specific and actionable instructions \r\n- **Context** - Relevant background details\r\n- **Format** - How the response should be structured\r\n- **Reference** - Additional examples or resources\r\n- **Tone** - The style in which the output is given\r\n:::",
